Totally normalâ€”youâ€™re running into two common Power Automate â€œgotchasâ€:

Variables donâ€™t always appear in the Dynamic content picker, especially inside sub-fields (like a Hyperlinkâ€™s Url/Description) or inside some connectorsâ€™ property editors.

Choice columns only accept one of the configured values (unless â€œAllow fill-in choicesâ€ is enabled). If your value isnâ€™t in the list, the picker wonâ€™t helpâ€”and the action may fail if you pass a non-allowed value.

Hereâ€™s how to wire each field right now.

How to use your variables anyway (two reliable options)
Option A â€” Use the Expression tab (fastest)

When a field doesnâ€™t show your variable in Dynamic content:

Click into the field.

Click Expression (next to Dynamic content).

Type one of these exactly and click Save:

Issue (text or choice):
variables('varIssue')

Description (multiline):
variables('varDescription')

Screenshot Attached? (Yes/No):
variables('varHasAttachment')

Link to user message (Url) (Hyperlink):
variables('varMessageLink')

For the Hyperlink Description sub-box, just type a literal like Open Teams message (no expression needed).

Option B â€” Surface them via Compose (so they appear in Dynamic content)

Add three quick Compose actions right before Create item:

Compose â€” IssueForList â†’ Expression: variables('varIssue')

Compose â€” DescriptionForList â†’ Expression: variables('varDescription')

Compose â€” HasAttachmentForList â†’ Expression: variables('varHasAttachment')

Then in Create item, pick Outputs from those three Composes. These will show up in the Dynamic content panel everywhere.
